{
  "texts": [
    "While the lowest is the student's previous educational features, with only a 4% of recurrence rate.",
    "From the percentage, it has been shown that most researchers have found that student activity features, such as time spent on the website studying, watching lectures, downloading files, and posting in discussion boards, to be the most significant predictors of student's performance.",
    "Moreover, it has been proven that the student academic features such as attendance, assignment, laboratory, and final grade are considered important factors, and not less than the importance of student activity features.",
    "Student academic and activity features are the only features that can be used alone in the predictive models.",
    "The use of student demographic features can be a valuable tool for understanding and improving student academic performance, however, it cannot be used by itself in the predictive model unless other features are added, except in Xiong et al (2022)."
  ]
}